Notes for my sample projects:

https://github.com/bazaarvoice/cloudformation-ruby-dsl

Converting a .json CloudFormation template:

- bundle install
- bundle exec cfntemplate-to-ruby [EXISTING_CFN] > [NEW_NAME.rb]
- chmod +x NEW_NAME.rb

Usage:

$ ./cms.rb
usage: ./cms.rb <expand|diff|validate|create|update|cancel-update|delete|describe|describe-resource|get-template>

Launching the CloudFormation stack:

- bundle exec ./cms.rb create --region us-west-2 --stack-name test-$(date '+%s') --disable-rollback --parameters "Environment=production"

Expand Ruby CloudFormation template into json:

- bundle exec ./cms.rb expand --parameters "Environment=production"

